race.comment: SIGIRIYA ROCK (8) did enough first up at Sale over 1427m, settling midfield and battling away well for fifth. He should be much fitter for that and did tackle some top races last time in, fifth to Evaporate at Randwick second up last time in. Suited to this trip now and can win. EMPHASIZE (4) might be an improver over more ground now at peak fitness. Look for a big run. THE MUFFIN MAN (5) returned from a spell with fair effort last start when seventh at Hamilton over 1600m. Blinkers back on and fitter over the longer trip could be a threat. QUELLO DORATO (11) was ordinary at Bendigo last start but was racing well prior. Blinkers go on and worth including.
